ANTHRAX - AZERBAIJAN (03): (SHAKI, ZERDAB) SHEEP, CATTLE, OIE
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Shaki, sheep
[2] Zerdab, sheep and cattle

******
[1] Shaki, sheep
Date: Thu 16 Jul 2020
Source: OIE [edited] https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=35060


Anthrax - Azerbaijan
--------------------
Information received on Thu 16 Jul 2020 from Dr Galib Abdulaliyev, Head, CVO, Animal Health Department, Azerbaijan Food Safety Agency, Baku, Azerbaijan

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 10 Jul 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 14 Jul 2020
Report date: 16 Jul 2020
Date submitted to OIE: 16 Jul 2020
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 9 May 2020
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Sheki, Aran, Sheki [Shaki]
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Jul 2020
Outbreak status: Resolved (16 Jul 2020)
Epidemiological unit: Backyard

Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 30 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 148 / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0

Affected population: 148 sheep and 30 cattle are in a backyard farm. The farmer has his own separate grazing pasture. Sheep are fed by grazing in the pasture. Only 2 young unvaccinated sheep were affected. All susceptible animals were vaccinated.

Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.00% / 0.00% / - / 0.00%
Sheep / 1.35% / 1.35% / 100.00% / 1.35%
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)

Epidemiological comments: Vaccination has been done in January [2020] lambing. Affected sheep were not vaccinated due to being less than 3 months of age during the last vaccination campaign.

Control measures:
Measures applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), quarantine, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, disinfection, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory of Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory) / Sheep / bacteriological examination / 14 Jul 2020 / Positive
Central Veterinary Laboratory of Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory) / Sheep / real-time PCR / 14 Jul 2020 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[For a map of outbreak locations, go to the OIE site. Aran is a village and municipality in the Shaki Rayon of Azerbaijan.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

