[2] Zerdab, sheep and cattle
Date: Fri 17 Jul 2020
Source: OIE [edited] https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=35091


Anthrax - Azerbaijan
--------------------
Information received on Fri 17 Jul 2020 from Dr Galib Abdulaliyev, Head, CVO, Animal Health Department, Azerbaijan Food Safety Agency, Baku, Azerbaijan

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 12 Jul 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 17 Jul 2020
Report date: 17 Jul 2020
Date submitted to OIE: 17 Jul 2020
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 9 May 2020
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Bayimly, Zardab [Zerdab]
Date of start of the outbreak: 12 Jul 2020
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm

Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 87 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 1000 / 4 / 4 / 0 / 0

Affected population: 1000 sheep and 87 cattle are in the farm. The farmer has his own separate grazing pasture. Sheep and cattle are grazing in the same pasture. All susceptible animals were vaccinated.

Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.15 % / 1.15 % / 100 % / 1.5 %
Sheep / 0.40 % / 0.40 % / 100 % / 0.40 %
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.).

Control measures:
Measures applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), quarantine, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, disinfection, no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory of Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 17 Jul 2020 / Positive
Central Veterinary Laboratory of Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory) / Cattle / real-time PCR / 17 Jul 2020 / Positive
Central Veterinary Laboratory of Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory) / Sheep / bacteriological examination / 17 Jul 2020 / Positive
Central Veterinary Laboratory of Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory) / Sheep / real-time PCR / 17 Jul 2020 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[For a map of outbreak locations, go to the OIE site.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This outbreak, like the one in May 2020, involves sheep, but this one also includes cattle.

Anthrax is a zoonotic disease that represents a threat to human and veterinary health in many parts of the world. Control of anthrax depends on several factors, including proper management of outbreaks and livestock vaccination, which have been implemented. Proper disposal of the infected animals is also key to controlling and limiting the disease. - Mod.TG

HealthMap/ProMED map:
Azerbaijan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7591145,134]
